No, he - he used to get a little pay, not much. I think it were five shilling for the first hours and half a crown each hours after. And that was when they had to fetch the houses out and - put them in. The Fire Brigade, you know, the fire engine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7999576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6713198\charrsid14555338 It was a horse drawn fire engine was it?
