 was your money, it was your money, you went in like - instead of putting it in a bank you put it - it went in this tank and - and had your - well we could draw it out when we wanted, you know, same as you had these - like war savings, yes. It was a war s
a
vings - it was a war saving effort and we went up and had one - I don't if it was fifteen shillings or twelve shilling out of this - from this tank, but we thought we were doing great having this. Yes. I don't - not only that, we were - we didn't draw it 
o
ut we took it in, we thought we were doing great because we went in this tank and had it - you know. Ni, it isn't. The war was ended and they brought these tanks up Hanley, for you to go - look at 'em, and you could have a certificate - a war certificate 
